headline: Two Allies Draw Map With Voters in Mind
abstract: The Israeli-Palestinian peace plan unveiled by President Trump and Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sounds more like a road map for their own futures than for the Middle East.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” A president trying to prevail in an impeachment trial stood with an Israeli prime minister under indictment on Tuesday to announce a long-delayed plan for resolving the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, and the result sounded more like a road map for their own futures than for the Middle East.
keywords: Trump-Ukraine Whistle-blower Complaint and Impeachment Inquiry
